{"title":"The Cannondale SuperX is Back","link":"https://theradavist.com/cannondale-superx-2025/","date":1739286014000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_Super_X_2025-01.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_Super_X_2025-01.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_Super_X_2025-01.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_Super_X_2025-01.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/cannondale/\" target=\"_blank\">Cannondale</a>‘s legendary <a href=\"https://www.cannondale.com/en-us/bikes/road/gravel/superx\" target=\"_blank\">SuperX</a> ‘cross bike is back as a lightweight and racing-focused gravel road bike. The brand has done a bang-up job on this resurrection, so let’s check it out.</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-06.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-06.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-06.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-06.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.cannondale.com/en-us/bikes/road/gravel/superx\" target=\"_blank\">SuperX</a> is BACK, reborn as a stripped down, souped up, pure gravel race machine—purpose-built for chasing podiums and PRs everywhere from Kansas to the local lunch-ride world championships. Its predecessor, the SuperSix EVO SE, set the fastest time ever for Unbound Gravel in 2024, and with the new SuperX, Cannondale has gone all in to make it even faster. Less aero drag. More fatigue-fighting compliance. Sleeker integration, and of course, less weight.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-05.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-05.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-05.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-05.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>While it’s designed for all-out gravel road racing, the SuperX doesn’t forget its ‘cross roots, so throw some 33 mm tires on it and point it straight through the sand pits, mud holes, and shoulder it up the steep climbs.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-01.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-01.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-01.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-01.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-03.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-03.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-03.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-03.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-02.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-02.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-02.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_SuperX_2025-02.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>SuperX Quick Hits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>70 x 48 mm tire clearance</li>\n<li>Sub 900 g frame weight on LAB71 Model</li>\n<li>Internal cable routing</li>\n<li>12x142mm thru-axle</li>\n<li>UDH</li>\n<li>BSA 68mm threaded BB</li>\n<li>Flat mount disc</li>\n<li>Integrated seatpost binder</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_Super_X_2025-Geo.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_Super_X_2025-Geo.png?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_Super_X_2025-Geo.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/Cannondale_Super_X_2025-Geo.png?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Geometry</h3>\n<p>A slacker head angle and a steeper seat angle mean this bike is intended to be ridden all-out, resulting in a mid-to-high-trail riding experience.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/C25_LAB71_SuperX_BMB-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/C25_LAB71_SuperX_BMB-2.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/C25_LAB71_SuperX_BMB-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/C25_LAB71_SuperX_BMB-2.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>LAB71 SuperX</strong> Frame $5,500 Complete $15,000 RAM RED AXS, 13-speed</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/C25_SuperX_Crb_2_CAS-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/C25_SuperX_Crb_2_CAS-2.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/C25_SuperX_Crb_2_CAS-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/C25_SuperX_Crb_2_CAS-2.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>SuperX 2</strong> $6,800 Shimano GRX 825 Di2</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/C25_SuperX_Crb_3_RAW-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/C25_SuperX_Crb_3_RAW-2.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/C25_SuperX_Crb_3_RAW-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/02/C25_SuperX_Crb_3_RAW-2.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>SuperX 3</strong> $4,200 Shimano GRX 820</p>\n<h3>Build Kits and Pricing</h3>\n<p>See more on complete kit breakdown at <a href=\"https://www.cannondale.com/en-us/bikes/road/gravel/superx\" target=\"_blank\">Cannondale</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/cannondale-superx-2025/\">The Cannondale SuperX is Back</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"5aeb84f53c667dbf4be481cb3aaa8184f27a088568944c084122bf5417b0337c","category":"Cycling"}